-- Sub-Sahara Africa Stocks: Safaricom, Sasini of Kenya Are Active
-- B y   C h r i s   K a y
-- 2012-01-13T15:32:39Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-13/sub-sahara-africa-stocks-safaricom-sasini-of-kenya-are-active.html
Kenya’s  All-Share Index (NSEASI)  fell for the
first time in seven days, dropping 1.4 percent to 55.03 in
Nairobi.  Mauritius’s  SEMDEX Index (SEMDEX)  rose for the first time in five
days, adding 0.1 percent to 1,873.27 by the end of trading. The
 FTSE/Namibia Overall Index (FTN098)  gained for a second day, increasing
0.6 percent to 878.82 in Windhoek. The  Nigerian Stock Exchange
All-Share Index (NGSEINDX)  declined 0.2 percent to 20,840.97 at the close
in Lagos, according to an e-mailed statement from the bourse.  The following shares were active in sub-Saharan Africa,
excluding South Africa. Stock symbols are in parentheses.  Safaricom Ltd. (SAFCOM)  , Kenya’s biggest mobile-phone
operator, rose 1.6 percent to 3.2 shillings, the highest close
since Sept. 26, as investors from abroad added to their holdings
following the company’s customer gains last year.  “At the current prices, we have been seeing increasing
levels of demand following price weaknesses that allows fund
managers and foreign investors to accumulate,” Gregory Waweru,
a research analyst at Nairobi-based Kestrel Capital East Africa
Ltd., said in a phone interview today.  Sasini Ltd. (STCL)  , a Kenyan tea and coffee producer,
climbed for a second day with a 2.8 percent gain, the biggest
increase since Nov. 10, to close at 12.95 shillings, after tea
prices rose at the latest auction of the leaf.  To contact the reporter on this story:
